. Thiespecies was previously recorded from “Central Asia” (
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B14FF9DAA4FFC78471CFBCBFA8F" author="Hampson, G. F." box="[905,1136,1303,1329]" pageId="26" pageNumber="127" pagination="172 - 291" refId="ref22932" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1899) A revision of the moths of the subfamily Pyraustinae and family Pyralidae. Part II. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 67 (1), 172 - 291. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1899. tb 06856. x" type="journal article" year="1899">Hampson 1899: 242</bibRefCitation>
); it was also recorded from “Kuldja” in adjacent area of 
<collectingCountry id="F3007675FF9DAA4FFDF64730FDF1FAEB" box="[519,586,1339,1365]" name="China" pageId="26" pageNumber="127">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF864B14FF9DAA4FFDA94730FCA4FAEB" author="Caradja, A." box="[600,799,1339,1365]" pageId="26" pageNumber="127" pagination="3 - 88" refId="ref21923" refString="Caradja, A. (1916) Beitrag zur Kenntnis der geographischen Verbreitung der Pyraliden und Tortriciden des europaischen Faunengebietes, nebst Beschreibung neuer Formen. Deutsche entomologische Zeitschrift Iris, 30 (1), 3 - 88." type="journal article" year="1916">Caradja 1916: 32</bibRefCitation>
